  "text": "Furthermore, the study of gender metadiscourse phenomenon has also been underexplored in Persian language. Ädel (2006: 198) emphasizes that gender of the writer could influence how much or what type of metadiscourse is used. This study then aims to redress the issue by dealing with this aspect of Persian linguistic behavior. The research addresses issues such as the extent in which similarities and differences can be found in the use of interactional metadiscourse markers by male and female candidates in thesis defenses. To this end, the papar adopts the model of community of practice suggested by [CITATION_1] with the aim of providing a more accurate interpretation of discourse interaction in contrast to other approaches (dominance and difference approaches).",
